{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at a module handoff boundary (collectors/aggregator -> summarizer), not a single-function algorithm. Use in-process fakes for the three source clients and assert the summarizer input contains all three payloads. Rejected System because behavior text is about \"content passed\" completeness, not real network/OS effects. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness does not depend on model judgment or multi-agentic sequencing.","test_description":"Wire real report orchestration modules with fake metrics API, fake issue-tracker client, and fake deployment-log reader returning distinct sentinel values; run one report build and assert the exact object sent to summary generation contains all three sections with correct mapping.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module error propagation and fallback rendering (source adapter failure -> report assembly), which requires wiring multiple components. A controlled fake failing source reproduces the failure boundary without real OS/network. Rejected System because behavior text focuses on fallback behavior, not real transport semantics. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because requirement is deterministic presence of a `data unavailable` section note, not model-quality judgment.","test_description":"Run the report pipeline with two sources returning valid data and one source stub raising the same exception type the adapter emits; verify execution completes, output includes a `data unavailable` marker for only that section, and no global abort/uncaught exception occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real summary-generation output quality (factual faithfulness to inputs), which a stub would always hide. This is exactly model decision quality, not just routing/retries. Rejected Workflow because behavior states one summary-generation step, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Use a fixed dataset with known key values, call the real summary generator model, and evaluate factual consistency against a rubric (for example required value mentions and contradiction checks) across repeated runs with pass-rate thresholds to account for nondeterminism.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external APIs and real email delivery/inbox receipt, so OS/network behavior is integral. Mocking delivery can hide real SMTP/API/auth/routing failures. Rejected Agentic because behavior text is about end-to-end delivery to inbox, not judging model output quality; any summary content can be treated as payload for this test. Rejected Workflow because no multi-agentic decision chain is specified.","test_description":"Execute the script in an end-to-end environment against real (or production-like) source endpoints and real email service/test inbox; assert one run produces an email received by configured recipients with expected report sections and metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on real service unreachability and cross-run retry behavior; real network failure modes and process/run boundaries are key. Mocks can miss actual connection/error semantics that trigger fallback and retry paths. Rejected Workflow because requirement is reliability state transition across runs, not multiple model decisions.","test_description":"Run once with email endpoint intentionally unreachable (for example blocked SMTP/API host) and verify report is persisted to fallback file; run the next scheduled invocation with service restored and verify previously saved report is retried and delivered, then cleared from pending state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.67,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
